            <div style="text-align: justify;font-family:calibri;font-size:16px;margin: 2px 21px;">

                This application platform, named IXDOT Repo (repurchase agreement) is designed as an inter-bank
                trading platform meant for users to buy and sell liquid collateral via a sale and buy-back (or a buy
                and sell back) transaction. Primary users of this application will be treasury dealers with Banks.<br /><br />
                Secondary users will be the fund managers with asset management companies, insurers, pension
                funds, hedge funds, family offices etc. The main objective for using this application is for users to
                manage their pool of quality assets that financial institutions hold by changing its quantity based on
                a collateral hierarchy maintained by the users. The platform is not restricted to banks who are
                governed by liquidity thresholds but can also be used by any participant who has a need to either
                improve its liquidity position to meet regulatory liquidity rules, or augment its yields.<br /><br />
                The platform provides a framework of asset portfolios that participants can peruse, provide pricing
                indicators, and ultimately trade to manage their liquidity profiles. The platform brings together
                participants with surplus liquidity and matches them with those who have a need to improve their
                liquidity position, and vice versa. The economic ownership of the assets remain vested with the
                counterparties and there is no need therefore for a sale.<br /><br />
                From the standpoint of the liquidity provider, the following considerations merit a mention:<br />
                <div style="text-align: justify;font-family:calibri;font-size:16px">
                    <ul>
                        <li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;It provides yield enhancing opportunities</li>

                        <li>
                            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The bank receives insurance for providing liquidity through over-collateralisation or
                            additional margining
                        </li>

                        <li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event of counterparty default, the lower quality asset is available for liquidation</li>

                        <li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; It provides a comparison of yields from various borrowers</li>

                    </ul>
                </div>
                IXDOT Repo works on a stand-alone basis as a trading platform and can be bundled with Kamakura
                Corporation’s KRIS (Kamakura Risk Information Services) providing a comprehensive trading
                platform and risk management capabilities.<br /><br />
                From a borrower (bank with a need for liquidity)
                perspective, the following considerations accrue:<br />
                <div style="text-align: justify;font-family:calibri;font-size:16px">
                    <ul>
                        <li style="padding-left: 15px;">It improves liquidity quickly</li>

                        <li style="padding-left: 15px;">It is cheaper than liquidating low quality assets for higher quality</li>

                        <li style="padding-left: 15px;">It provides the borrower with multiple choices and avenues</li>

                        <li style="padding-left: 15px;">
                            It provides an uptick in the LCR metric immediately if the repo holding period is less than 30
                            days and improves NSFR if the period is less than a year
                        </li>

                        <li style="padding-left: 15px;">The transaction is Central Bank approved</li>

                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
